<DOC><DOCNO> AP881221-0229 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-21-88 0900EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-OPEC-Iraq     12-21 0143</FIRST><SECOND>BC-OPEC-Iraq,0150</SECOND><HEAD>Iraq Promises Adherence To OPEC Quotas</HEAD><DATELINE>LAGOS, Nigeria (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Iraq has pledged to srictly abide by OPEC'srecent production agreement and is asking other members to do thesame, OPEC President Rilwanu Lukman says.   The government-owned Lagos Times reported Wednesday that Lukmanhad received a letter from Iraqi Oil Minister Issam Al Chalabipromising strict adherence to the production agreement reached lastmonth by the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries.   The cartel agreed to cut daily production to 18.5 million barrelsto help drive up sagging worldwide oil prices.   In the letter to Lukman, the Iraqi minister said compliance wasnecessary ``so that the objectives of our organization are fulfilledand the interest of all member countries served.''   The minister also said that Kuwait and Saudi Arabia would stopsending war relief crude oil to Iraq from Jan. 1.</TEXT></DOC>